<h1>Problem 1427 - 2020 IMOSL, G7, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(P\) be a point on the circumcircle of acute triangle \(ABC\). Let \(D,E,F\) be the reflections of \(P\) in the \(A\)-midline, \(B\)-midline, and \(C\)-midline. Let \(\omega\) be the circumcircle of the triangle formed by the perpendicular bisectors of \(AD, BE, CF\).</p>
<p>Show that the circumcircles of \(\triangle ADP, \triangle BEP, \triangle CFP,\) and \(\omega\) share a common point.</p>
